    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-04-02T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-04-02T06:00:00-05:00" n="566"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.4121/289: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-04-02T11:00:00+00:00"
                            >April 2, 1936—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 2—7:33 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>171. Department’s 55, February 15, 1 p.m. Foreign Office hopes full powers for
                    the signature of the Convention in respect of the United Kingdom, Australia and
                    New Zealand will be ready for despatch to British Ambassador, Washington, early
                    next week and agrees that accessions to the original Convention of 1899, as
                    supplemented by the Convention of 1902, will remain unaffected by the coming
                    into operation of the supplementary Convention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[For text of supplementary convention between the United States and the
                        United Kingdom, Australia, and New Zealand respecting the <pb facs="0800"
                            n="720" xml:id="pg_720"/> tenure and disposition of real and personal
                        property, signed at Washington, May 27, 1936, see Department of State Treaty
                        Series No. 964, or 55 Stat. 1101.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
